problem:
In the figure below, side $AE$ of rectangle $ABDE$ is parallel to the $x$-axis, and side $BD$ contains the point $C$. The vertices of triangle $ACE$ are $A(1, 1)$, $C(3, 3)$ and $E(4, 1)$. What is the ratio of the area of triangle $ACE$ to the area of rectangle $ABDE$? Express your answer as a common fraction.

[asy]unitsize(1inch);
draw((0,0)--(4.5,0),Arrow);
draw((0,0)--(0,3.5),Arrow);
draw((-0.1,1)--(0.1,1));
draw((-0.1,2)--(0.1,2));
draw((-0.1,3)--(0.1,3));
draw((1,0.1)--(1,-0.1));
draw((2,0.1)--(2,-0.1));
draw((3,0.1)--(3,-0.1));
draw((4,0.1)--(4,-0.1));
draw((1,1)--(1,3)--(4,3)--(4,1)--cycle);
draw((1,1)--(3,3)--(4,1));
fill((1,1)--(3,3)--(1,3)--cycle,gray(0.7));
fill((3,3)--(4,3)--(4,1)--cycle,gray(0.7));
label("$A$",(1,1),SW);
label("$B$",(1,3),NW);
label("$C$",(3,3),N);
label("$D$",(4,3),NE);
label("$E$",(4,1),SE);
[/asy]

